      "side": 1,
      "message": "I was able to make the imageID in the format \"runID/{nopatch/withpatch}/rank/URLfilename\" by making ImagePath return two strings, one for the local file path and the other for the GS path. This enabled me to reconstruct the YYYY/MM/DD directories as they appear in GS in the ImagePath implementation and also specify different paths for storing/accessing images locally and downloading images from GS in ImageLoader. However, I wasn\u0027t sure if having ImagePath return two strings, or just having two separate functions (LocalPath and GSPath) made more sense in terms of design -- what do you think? \n\nNow that I look at it, it should probably be called ImagePaths if we go with the return two paths approach, but I\u0027ll wait for your input about the design before uploading another patch.\n\nAlso, I removed most \"digest\" references in imgloader.go because the abovementioned change made using the word digest not make much sense in most of the functions. I started working on doing the same for mem_diffstore.go but soon realized that unlike imgloader, the module is not really self-contained and would require changes to interfaces in different files as well. I held off on changing these just in case you think the renaming belongs in a different CL; please let me know!",
      "revId": "1c210e2dffa4783b42ddb29e4db0a47ff4f6b225",
