      "side": 1,
      "message": "I did need to prepend the dir in order to get this working properly, but just calling ImagePath to get the local file path was fine for both cases. I verified with local runs of skia_diff_server with GoldIDPathMapper and chromium-skia-gm/dm-images-v1, and PixelDiffIDPathMapper and cluster-telemetry/tasks/pixel_diff_runs. I think this makes sense because the current implementation calls fileutil.TwoLevelRadixPath(path) for both images and diff images; as long as the frontend for either server constructs URLs in a manner consistent with how image names and paths were created, this should work fine.\n\nIt would get a bit messy if you still did want to break it down by case, as DiffIDs for both Gold and PixelDiff are colon-separated, but in the URL request they will be separated by hyphens and slashes, respectively. So doing something like strings.Join([]string{dir, m.mapper.DiffPath(m.mapper.SplitDiffID(imgID))}, \"/\") wouldn\u0027t work for diff images.",
      "revId": "1c210e2dffa4783b42ddb29e4db0a47ff4f6b225",
